Hey everyone, first season using path planner and using a swerve to do autonomous. I wanted to start by tuning its PID , I’m using the YAGSL library and to be honest I have some problems that are kinda strange, the first one is that no matter what if I change the PID , it stills goes faster that it should according to what the PathPlanner telemetry says.

image 906×158 8.88 KB

The second problem is that a made a simple path just moving 3M going to position (3.40, 2.5) and having a start point of (.4, 2.5). And each time i put enable does a completely different path that it should make.

image 1919×1029 87.7 KB

image 1919×1029 87.7 KB

image 1919×1029 87.7 KB

The third thing is that according to my dashboard the robot doesn’t start at the correct start position and moves my path to a curve and then go straight for the first attempt, the rest of them do completely weird things. Im goingto put a video that could explain better what i mean

I don’t know if it’s because i have the robot suspended on the air or because the configuration of my swerve at YAGSL is wrong, if this happened to someone or has an idea of what could it be would be great some help please. Thank you all!

Do you see how your Robot Velocity and Robot Angular velocity on that page don’t nake any sense whatsoever?

Have you tried on the carpet yet?

Tl;dr tune your PP PIDs or figure out what telemetry is very very wrong
